        <detaileddescription>
<para>The default conversion operator <ndash/> where the actual conversion happens.</para>
<para>Specialisations (i.e. for new convert-types) must define their own version of this function <parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>sv</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>A string_view (implicitly converted from std::strings) representing a value to be converted </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>A value of type T corresponding to the input string </para>
</simplesect>
<parameterlist kind="exception"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>logic_error</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>If the characters could not be converted into numerics (i.e. ab) </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>logic_error</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>If some, but not all, characters could be converted into numerics (i.e. 123ab) </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>logic_error</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>If the result is out of range (i.e. convert&lt;int&gt;(INT_MAX + 10)) </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
